						<div class="postbody">Yes, using external nametables only.  To clarify, by &quot;through the mapper&quot;, I mean the mapper (CPLD the way I'm imagining it) would be driving the address bus of the external CHR memory.  So yeah, the AND logic would be like:<br /><br />CHR-RAM A0 = PPU-A0 &amp;&amp; !NT_ACCESS<br />CHR-RAM A5 = PPU-A5 &amp;&amp; !NT_ACCESS<br /><br />(NT_ACCESS excludes attribute table access)<br /><br />edit: This made me think too, staying within 64 metatiles (as we normally have to with 256 tiles), a mapper could use the upper 2 bits of the nametable data as the attribute (so metatile $40 would be the same as metatile $00, but the next color).  Eliminate the attribute table entirely. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

